{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:18:08.370961+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e0f90ac88e1236616df18600c7f7a5f80ac113c6)", "id": "lc_6f71a9d3-fae1-4a26-b4d3-fcab1127b35f"}, {"type": "text", "text": "from datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom typing import Any, Dict\n\nfrom fastapi.security import OAuth2PasswordBearer\nfrom jose import jwt\n\nfrom app.services import BaseService\nfrom app.settings import settings\n\n# for authentication that works seamlessly with OpenAPI\nreuseable_oauth = OAuth2PasswordBearer(\n    tokenUrl=\"/api/v1/user/login\",\n    scheme_name=\"JWT\"\n)\n\n\ndef hash_password(password: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Creates a hash of the password\"\"\"\n    hashed_password = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.hash(password)\n    return hashed_password\n\n\ndef verify_password(plain_password: str, hashed_password: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Checks if a password corresponds to a hash\"\"\"\n    password_is_verified = settings.PASSWORD_HASHER.verify(\n        plain_password, hashed_password\n    )\n\n    return bool(password_is_verified)\n\n\ndef create_auth_token(payload: Dict[str, Any], expiry: int) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    This handles the encoding of user information into a token\n    that can be used. It is generic so as to accomodate access and\n    refresh token.\n    \"\"\"\n    expiry_delta = datetime.now() + timedelta(seconds=expiry)\n    data_to_encode = {\"expiry\": str(expiry_delta), \"data\": payload}\n    encoded_data: str = jwt.encode(\n        data_to_encode, settings.SECRET_KEY, settings.JWT_ALGORITHM\n    )\n\n    return encoded_data\n\n\nclass UserService(BaseService):\n    \"\"\"\n    This class helps perform bulk of activities required by the corresponding API\n    \"\"\"\n    def a_method(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Here, the use of `self.save` is demonstrated.\n        Ensure to take out this method.\n        \"\"\"\n        model_instance = ...\n        self.save(model_instance)", "id": "lc_744ffd23-fac3-40b8-b0ec-b477712ea237"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "7c159e04-58cb-4efb-95a2-ea64f5d227aa", "tool_call_id": "call_41a205b483444189984fa26e", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:18:20.580104+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a comprehensive summary of the main Python dependency and service stack used by this FastAPI template:\n\n---\n\n## **Framework & Server**\n| Component | Technology |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **Web Framework** | **FastAPI** (with `[all]` extras — includes `uvicorn`, `pydantic`, `starlette`, etc.) |\n| **ASGI Server** | **Uvicorn** (as seen in `main.py`) |\n\n---\n\n## **Database**\n| Component | Technology |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **Database** | **PostgreSQL** (via the `postgres` Docker image) |\n| **Async Driver** | **asyncpg** — async PostgreSQL driver |\n| **Sync Driver** | **psycopg2** — traditional PostgreSQL adapter |\n| **Database Abstraction** | **databases[postgresql]** — async database layer |\n| **ORM / Schema** | **SQLAlchemy** (pulled in via `databases` + `sqlalchemy-utils`) |\n| **Migrations** | **Alembic** (both `alembic` Python package and `alembic.ini` config present) |\n\n---\n\n## **Authentication**\n| Component | Technology |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **JWT Tokens** | **python-jose[cryptography]** — used in `auth/services.py` via `jose.jwt.encode()` for creating auth tokens |\n| **Password Hashing** | **passlib[bcrypt]** — used through `settings.PASSWORD_HASHER` with `hash()` and `verify()` methods |\n| **OAuth2 Flow** | **FastAPI's built-in `OAuth2PasswordBearer`** — configured with `tokenUrl=\"/api/v1/user/login\"` |\n| **Form Parsing** | **python-multipart** — required by FastAPI for form-data (login forms) |\n\n---\n\n## **Redis**\n| Component | Technology |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **Redis Client** | **aioredis** — async Redis client |\n| **Redis Server** | **redis:alpine** (Docker image, port 6379) |\n\nRedis is declared as a dependency and runs as a Docker Compose service, though it wasn't directly invoked in the sampled code — likely used for caching, session storage, or rate limiting.\n\n---\n\n## **Testing**\n- **pytest** is listed as a top-level dependency (not dev-only), and an `auth/tests/` directory exists.\n\n---\n\n## **Infrastructure Summary (Docker Compose)**\n```\nweb        → Python 3.9 (FastAPI + Uvicorn) on port 11000\npostgres   → PostgreSQL on port 5432\nredis      → Redis Alpine on port 6379\n```\n\nIn short, this is a **FastAPI + PostgreSQL (async) + Redis + JWT/bcrypt auth** template with Alembic for database migrations, managed via Pipenv and containerized with Docker Compose.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 622, "prompt_tokens": 9091, "total_tokens": 9713, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 12, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8576, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007960386, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002548986, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00054114}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863488-Pjk53RT2VXhoy3v2pcdf", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3bc-5174-7423-80af-d2619e3c2d33-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9091, "output_tokens": 622, "total_tokens": 9713, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8576}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 12}}}}]}}}
